{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea21594d-40aa-421e-9e66-331a7ef4cf32","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates **`.ips` crash reports** when a process crashes. You don't need `createdump`.\n\n**Where to find them:**\n\n- **User crashes:** `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`\n- **System crashes:** `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`\n\nLook for a file named like `<YourAppName>-<date>.ips`.\n\n**Quick way to find the latest one:**\n\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips | head -5\n```\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them in a GUI.\n\n**For a core dump** (if you need one for `lldb`), run this *before* reproducing the crash:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\nCore dumps go to `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\n> **Tip:** If you have a `.ips` file with native frames from `libcoreclr.so` or the NativeAOT runtime, I can help symbolicate it — just ask!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"218d1476-9347-4c22-b789-aed1fb790388","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a knowledge question about macOS crash reporting, not a code task. Let me answer directly.","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"9808:222DF7:B39BD1:D401FA:69F40645"},"id":"62154285-69b5-44b0-8639-1fb0bed7c0f4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:47:58.667Z","parentId":"95855162-0449-4854-ae40-f29475355bd1"}
